column10:
Coffee, tea, gin, whiskey... whatever took your fancy.
We talked, you watched, I listened.
I walked away, but you stayed.
You said you cared, but you didn't.
column11:
Having a talk can be hard
Everyone is on their guard
I asked him to sit
and explained it was time to split

column10:
The samurai ate a sandwich for lunch.
He ate it with his chopsticks.
I watched him as he ate it.
And then he went and dropped it.
column11:
Bloody battles awaits for our sword wielding friend.
Contest of steel upon steel, till only one is left in the end.
Protected his most precious item from the fiends now all bloody.
But a sandwich, his favorite meal, ham cheese mustard and honey.

column3: The AI is very competent, some features are definitely more useful than others though.
column10:
I’m taking a trip, with stops at zoos, aquariums.
I want to see a polar bear! I’ll take photos of penguins.
And in the travels i have made.
I feel now a profound satisfaction.
column11:

Is it the long road trips?
That consist of friends and eating chips?
Or is it the memories we make on the trip

column3: Having more options to choose from, a larger pool, would be a help.

The sailor's mate; when the seas tighten.
I'll find my way back to my native shore.
Then sigh no more.

No real hopes, apathetic indecision
Every day was like being on a boat
With no direction all I do is float

column3: I think it works very fine and I wish I had this whenever I had writer's block.
column10:
The storm grew fiercer and fierce.
As we escaped, we screamed.
Fear is a stumbling block.
And it's getting harder to breathe.
Then all the world was dead.
Before I could say a peep
With black birds swarming around our heads.
We were lost in the deep.
column11:
He left me breathless
I felt like a mess
Trying to figure out my feelings gave me stress
I did want to eventually confess

column10:
There once was a man who was abducted.
They covered his head in a bucket.
The man was confused and didn't know what to do.
So he dashed and caused a ruckus.

Mother earth could get no rest.
Inspite of always trying her best.
It was because her heart was shattered.
As planet earth, smothered by the weight, lies bare and tattered.
column11:
Climate change is caused by us
Now the world is making a fuss
We acted a bit sus
and now this happened because of us

Into the depths of the ocean.

So I'll just keep swimming.

column3: I know it might be too much, could I set up a theme in the beginning and all my following instructions would be framed within the theme of the poem, which could be very helpful. In general the AI is quite useful.

column3: The rhyming words for sure need help. A lot don't come to rhyming. Also, sometimes when you ask it to suggest the next sentence, it doesn't copy over the previous sentence, and gets you to copy it in before suggesting anything.
column9: Desire is a thorn you can't snuff out
column10:
Is bliss, then, such concupiscence as this.
A savage lust for naught but a moment
A lone, solitary pleasure - dismissed,
By all, but you, my one true opponent
column11:

You're alone too, but your wife is at home
What's the harm of saying hello?
As you ask yourself you already know
column12: Desire is a thorn you can't snuff out

column3: I wanted an option that combine the "write a line related to the previous line" and "write a line ending with a word that rhymes with ____". Also, it is terrible at rhyming words. Some "rhymes" aren't even close/explainable by English pronunciation quirks ("near and we"?!?). Also, maybe a "memory bank" of suggested lines? A couple of times I remembered a previous line that would work well later in the poem, but it was gone and other than just typing it in, I couldn't figure out how to get it back.
column10:
And the bells are chiming in the steeples.
And the sun is shining on the fields;
And birds are singing somewhere near
But then he was gone, and i felt fear.
column11:
What is a false day?
It is a day that is not real
It is a day that nothing is what it seems
That is a false day

column3: A good task overall and the tool seems to work fine.
column10:
Hold him a while.
Tell him you need a friend.
Our relationship is a tangle of weeds.
But I'll embrace him until the end.
You know me like a friend,
I love you like a foe.
column11:
There's no rule that says you have to be nice
When it came to being mean you didn't think twice
But one day you apologized for all you'd did wrong
You said you wanted to be friends all along

column10:
That the world is a vast, boundless ocean.
But people with brains have another notion.
The 'freedom' that you speak of is an illusion;
I have arrived at one conclusion.
I have no love for my own soul.
column11:
It's a free country, but you pay to live
Working everyday, your time you must give
Working is essential, you must try your best
You might as well be chained to your desk

column3: The best part of the tool is getting help with words at the end of a sentence and then being able to build off that.
column10:
And you are the one who set the trap.
The ideas that lingered fell apart real fast.
Lust is a mighty thief.
Wherever it goes, it gives no remorse.
And I feel it as my own heart.
That we are better on our own.
Knowing we were better apart.
I'd rather leave you all alone.

I'll be there for you, I am your friend.
I'll listen to you vent, I will not judge.
I’ll hold your hand, I will not leave.
I’ll be there for you, I swear.
column11:
A warm cup of coffee on a winter day
Staying in bed, wasting the day away
A friend calls you up and wants to come over
Movies and games while the storm passes over

column10:
My dreams shatter like a glass ceiling
As you walk away, dragging a broken shard
I watch you leave, you no longer have meaning
As I lay there in the dark, my heart turns hard
column11:
Bashing my head against the ceiling,
again and again, till it shatters.
if I can't make it, I'll help the next person,
by all that's holy, I hope this matters.

column3: The AI is very competent. Not sure about the feature "suggest a topic", it asks for a specific word in a sentence rather than a topic word which doesn't have to be included in the sentence.
column10:
Time was when a man would die for glory.
But now, all that's left is ash.
Death comes like a cold wind, thudding of a door closing after а party.
Only leaving the old woman with a feeling of sadness.
column11:
Is this glory in vain?
Did we really have to suffer through all this pain?
What did we gain
If this glory was in vain

column3: This time I used the feature where you put in a whole sentence and it comes up with one to follow which I liked a lot. Very good tool that I would love to keep using for when I write.
column10:
The sky has become for us a bed.
For we lay asleep and pray to the stars.
Dreaming is a way to forget the pain.
Is but a relief from the heaviness in my head.
Tomorrow we wake to escape from today.
Remember where we once were at the start. 
And how much we've changed.
column11:
Wagon travels through rain and shine,
Sagen counts his fingers day and night;
"when will we arrive, Papa?"
"Just appreciate how far we've come, son."

there was so much to shoulder
